40 (B) Assess the feasibility of implementing a registry in Georgia, including potential
41 costs, administrative procedures, and due process protections;
42 (C) Examine the potential impact of such a registry on employment and hiring
43 practices in health and caregiving professions;
44 (D) Consider appropriate mechanisms for appeals and removal from the registry;
45 (E) Identify necessary legislative and regulatory changes to establish and maintain such
46 a registry; and
47 (F) Solicit input from relevant stakeholders, including advocacy organizations, care
48 providers, law enforcement, and the public on how to improve service delivery for
49 people with disabilities.
50 (4) Meetings. The chairperson shall call all meetings of the committee. The committee
51 may conduct such meetings at such places and at such times as it may deem necessary or
52 convenient to enable it to exercise fully and effectively its powers, perform its duties, and
53 accomplish the objectives and purposes of this resolution.
54 (5) Allowances, expenses, and funding.
55 (A) The legislative members of the committee shall receive the allowances provided
56 for in Code Section 28-1-8 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated.
57 (B) Members of the committee who are state officials, other than legislative members,
58 or who are state employees shall receive no compensation for their services on the
59 committee, but they may be reimbursed for expenses incurred by them in the
60 performance of their duties as members of the committee in the same manner as they
61 are reimbursed for expenses in their capacities as state officials or employees.
62 (C) The allowances authorized by this resolution shall not be received by any member
63 of the committee for more than five days unless additional days are authorized. Funds
64 necessary to carry out the provisions of this resolution shall come from funds
65 appropriated to the House of Representatives; except that funds for the reimbursement
66 of the expenses of state officials, other than legislative members, and for the
